<BR><B><I>
L Stevens,
UK
</I></B><P>
Being an American citizen, I feel ashamed of my government's biasedness and for its being blind towards the brutality and atrocities of the Israeli government. America had been a land of fair minded and just people but in the case of Palestine issue, our government's complete lack of conscience, fairness and justice will hurt our position as the leader of 'human rights and free world'. We cannot justify our position. Unless we take a non-partisan role, such brutality and arrogance may further accentuate in future.  
<BR><B><I>
Abdul Momen,
Boston, USA
</I></B><P>

</FONT><TABLE BGCOLOR="#FFFFCC" HSPACE="2" VSPACE="2" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="150" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="3" ALIGN="RIGHT">




<TR><TD><IMG  SRC="/web/20001203074700im_/http://news.bbc.co.uk/furniture/startquote.gif" WIDTH=23 HEIGHT=18 BORDER=0 VALIGN="TOP" ALT=""><BR><DIV CLASS="boxbody">
I am saddened that Jerusalem in 2000 is such a violent place - a far cry from the city I saw 15 years ago</DIV><IMG ALIGN="RIGHT" SRC="/web/20001203074700im_/http://news.bbc.co.uk/furniture/endquote.gif" WIDTH=23 HEIGHT=18 BORDER=0 VALIGN="ABSBOTTOM" ALT=""><BR CLEAR=ALL></TD></TR>

	
		<TR><TD BGCOLOR="CCCC99"><DIV CLASS="boxhead">
	
	



